When you are considering a surgeon for your surgery, it is important to do your research and find out about the surgeon's professional and personal history. 

Ask questions about the surgeon's background, education, certifications, and experience. It is also important to find out if the surgeon has any conflicts of interest. Find out what type of post-surgery care the surgeon will provide, and how long they will be available after your surgery.

Before deciding to work with a surgeon, it is important to get to know him or her. It is best to talk with your friends and family who have had work done by the doctor and ask them about their experience. It is also important to ask the doctor questions about his or her background.

No matter how good a surgeon is, it is important to know what you are getting into before deciding to work with them. You should know how long they have been practicing and what type of surgeries they specialize in. If you have any questions about the surgeon, ask them directly. They will be able to give you a straight answer and tell you if they have any other qualifications that would help you make your decision.

The decision to work with a surgeon is not one that should be taken lightly. It is important to get to know your surgeon before making the decision. Ask questions about the type of surgery you are undergoing, what their specialties are, and what their expertise is. When you find someone that you feel confident with, make sure to ask them for references so that you can speak with others who have worked with them.

✨The Sculptra Journey✨

Sculptra is a biostimulant injectable that helps your body produce collagen. It can be injected superficially to tighten the skin and visibly reduce wrinkles. It can also be injected deeper to replace lost volume. 

This beautiful patient received a total of four vials of Sculptra over a series of three treatments between 2/22-11/22. 

Results are always natural because unlike fillers, this product stimulates your body’s own collagen in a slow, natural process. It is a journey, as desired results usually take 2-4 treatments depending on severity of collagen and volume loss. 

These results will last years! Once your collagen is produced it is lost at a rate of about 1% per year-just like the rest of your collagen! 

Patients usually only need maintenance treatments once every few years.

This wonderful patient has had multiple injectable treatments in the past - during her assessment, I recognized that some of the fillers were not optimally placed, to the point of emphasizing some of her natural asymmetries & not addressing other areas of concern.

During an assessment, I take a global approach by considering every aspect of the patient from personality, age, skin tone/texture, etc. to ensure the comprehensive plan we create, benefits this patient and their individuality the most. 

Assessment, correction, & optimization takes time so we are extremely grateful to the patient for trusting us with this timeline, & thankful to @allerganaesthetics for providing such a diverse & comprehensive line of products to accomplish this.

The importance of choosing the right provider, & educating yourself on the correct product! 💉

This amazing patient had silicone injected in her pyriform area a long time ago (obviously not by me) when many of the amazing products we have today did not exist on the market! Over time the silicone became misplaced in the tissue & distorted, which led to some concerns of symmetry. 
I made a small incision within the natural crease of her peri-oral region so that any scar would be well disguised and also respective to her natural animation. 

As you can notice, the silicone had integrated with tissue and had to be dissected out piece by piece. Silicone does not metabolize/dissolve like regular fillers, so it has to be surgically removed. 
I can’t wait to follow her healing journey with you all!

The conversation amongst Non-surgical modalities (such as bio-stimulators, fillers, laser devices, threads, etc.) & and whether they have an impact on Face Lift and Neck Lift Surgery, has only increased in debate. It is undeniable that the realm of injectables and nonsurgical treatments has only increased in popularity, and only growing at an exponential rate. As a surgeon who also injects & utilizes many of these treatments, I perform surgery every day on patients who have received multiple Non-surgical treatments (both treated by myself & not by myself). In an attempt to gather a more global consensus regarding this conversation, @nayakplasticsurgery & I have created a survey specifically for Face/Neck Lift surgeons to take in an attempt to collect everyone’s experience with this subject. So, if you are a face/neck lift surgeon or even know one, please share this survey & take it! We are hoping to collect official responses and submit the findings for a peer-reviewed publication, & also curate a better understanding of this topic so we can inevitably improve both Non-surgical and surgical efforts, resulting in better & safer patient outcomes. 

⬇️
The link to this survey can be found in my bio!
